node.title: NBA Countdown on ABC after Bucks Game 3 victory

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing a sport and text that says 'P KG MIAMI 25 BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ'.

node.text: Free agent guard Kendrick Nunn has agreed to a two-year deal with the Los Angeles Lakers, source tells ESPN. Deal includes a player option. Nunn turned down significantly more money to chase a title with the Lakers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021 tagging @richpaul, @lucnewton, @5talen, and @klutchsports. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Restricted free agent Talen Horton-Tucker has agreed to a three-year $32M deal to stay with the Los Angeles Lakers, his agents Klutch Sports CEO Rich Paul and Lucas Newton tell ESPN.'.

node.text: Horton-Tucker is an important asset for the Lakers -- a young, 20 year-old ascending talent with a penchant for scoring. Lakers expect him to take a big step this season.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Q sharecare ATLANTA BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Free agent guard Tony Snell has agreed to a one-year deal with the Portland Trail Blazers, his agent Austin Brown of CAA Basketball tells ESPN.'.

node.text: Blazers add some shooting to their bench.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people playing sports, ball and text that says 'ibotta na BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Didi Louzada has agreed on a new four-year deal with the New Orleans Pelicans, his agent Aylton Tesch tells ESPN.'.
Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '5 ZENN CHIGAGO 10'.

node.text: Breaking: The Bulls are finalizing a sign-and-trade deal to acquire San Antonio’s DeMar DeRozan on a three-year, $85M contract  for Thad Young, Al-Farouq Aminu, a 2025 first-round pick, a 2022 second-round pick via the Lakers and a 2025 second-round pick, sources tell ESPN.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Rakuten DARLAND 34 $200M Contracts With Steph Curry agreeing to the largest average salary ever at $54 million, Octagon basketball has now negotiated the biggest total (Giannis $228M) and average deals in NBA history.'.

node.text: Two historic deals for @octagonbasketball with clients @stephencurry30 and @giannis_an34.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Free agent G Malik Monk has agreed to a deal with the Los Angeles Lakers, source tells ESPN.'.

node.text: Monk had his best season in Charlotte a year ago, shooting 40 percent from 3.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, ball and text that says 'wish LAKERS 7'.

node.text: Free agent F Carmelo Anthony has agreed to a one-year deal with the Los Angeles Lakers, his manager Bay Frazier tells ESPN.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021 tagging @warriors, @octagon, @stephencurry30, @davidsonbasketball, and @octagonbasketball. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
Two-time MVP @stephencurry30  has agreed on a four-year, $215M contract extension with the Golden State Warriors, making him the first player in history to sign two career $200 million-plus deals, his agent Jeff Austin of @octagonbasketball tells ESPN. 

Curry will extend his contract off his $45.8 million salary for 2021-22, which means he’s now guaranteed $261 million over the next five seasons.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021 tagging @brooklynnets, @caa_basketball, @balapat, and @australianboomers. May be an image of 2 people, people playing sports and text that says 'Frost 8 BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Free agent G Patty Mills has agreed to a two-year, $12M deal with the Brooklyn Nets, his agent Steven Heumann of CAA Basketball tells ESPN. Deal includes a player option.'.

node.text: Significant commitment for the Nets, who beat out several contenders for the longtime San Antonio Spur and Australian national player..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people playing sports and text that says 'GEICO washington BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Free agent c Robin Lopez has agreed to a one-year deal with the Orlando Magic, sources tell ESPN.'.

Photo by Adrian Wojnarowski on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing a sport, ball and text that says 'wish LAKERS JMOTVES BREAKING NEWS FROM WOJ Free agent C Andre Drummond has agreed to a one-year deal with the 76ers, source tells ESPN.'.
